{"id":"project-LICHEN-xql4","title":"CoapOption::as_uint silently truncates options longer than 4 bytes","description":"File: rust/lichen-coap/src/codec.rs
Line: 282-288

Category: CORRECTNESS

The as_uint() method interprets CoAP option values as u32 integers by shifting each byte into the accumulator. However, for options longer than 4 bytes, the upper bytes silently get shifted out:

```rust
pub fn as_uint(&self) -> u32 {
    let mut val = 0u32;
    for &b in self.value {
        val = (val << 8) | b as u32;
    }
    val
}
```

Example: for value [0x01, 0x02, 0x03, 0x04, 0x05], the result is 0x02030405 (0x01 silently discarded).

While RFC 7252 integer options are at most 4 bytes in valid messages, a malformed or malicious message could include longer option values. The function silently returns a wrong value instead of detecting the error.

Impact: Incorrect interpretation of malformed CoAP options could cause:
- Wrong Max-Age caching behavior
- Incorrect port numbers in Uri-Port
- Misinterpretation of Content-Format

Fix: Either validate that self.value.len() <= 4 and return Result/Option, or document that only the last 4 bytes are used.","status":"open","priority":3,"issue_type":"bug","owner":"me@mark.atwood.name","created_at":"2026-07-12T17:08:31.348556Z","created_by":"Mark Atwood","updated_at":"2026-07-12T17:08:31.348588Z"}

